The Administration may not begin construction of the new parallel transport runway, identified in the Airport Master Plan as runway 10 R/28L, until:
The Administration:
Adopts the proposed noise assistance programs for residential areas within the airport noise zone including, but not limited to:
Implements a pilot program of homeowner assistance in fiscal year 1988; and
The State Highway Administration completes construction of the following highway projects required in conjunction with airport improvements:
Hammonds Ferry Road/Poplar Avenue intersection improvements;
MD 170/Poplar Avenue intersection;
Poplar Avenue widening;
MD 176 widenings;
MD 176/Hammonds Ferry Road intersection;
Nursery Road/MD 295 interchange; and
MD 3/MD 176 interchange (auxiliary lane).
